(thirdQuint)Study of Tissue Samples From Patients With Glioma or Other Brain Tumors.

 OBJECTIVES: Primary - To better understand the pathophysiology of gliomas and identify molecular markers that may predict prognosis and progression or that could identify new therapeutic approaches.

 Secondary - To compare gene expression profiles, in terms of response to treatment, and attempt to isolate subgroups of patients with objective response to certain types of chemotherapy or radiotherapy.

 OUTLINE: This is a multicenter study.

 Biological samples are collected from patients at time of surgery for diagnostic and/or treatment purposes.

